snippet.textDisplay:
As of 25Mar, there are 80 deaths and 6,412 confirmed infections in NL ; ~1.25%. Keep in mind that NL is testing very sparingly. So, how many are actually infected? 2x? 5 x? 10x?
Beginning this week, blood donations will be screened for SARS-CoV2 antibodies (anonymously and with permission) to understand better the real infection rate.
I am confident that should the numbers change drastically, NL will go to a much stricter lockdown. As of today, people have already been fined for 'hanging out' in a group larger than 3 not more than 1.5 meters apart (for the metric-impaired that is ~5 feet)
As a member of a 'high risk group', I will be on the phone to the doctor at the first sign of any symptoms. Otherwise, I'll stay at home and watch videos that show not quite all for the story.

The problem is we currently don't fully understand COVID-19! People are reporting to test positive with ONLY GI symptoms. People are reporting to test positive with NO symptoms. Clearly this disease isn't affecting people the same way across the board, and we have no idea why that is. With reports of reinfection coming in from China and Japan early on in this crisis, we need to be asking : 1. how long immunity lasts IF it even is achievable, 2. Are we prepared to allow coronavirus to run its course on our population KNOWING that it can permanently damage peoples' lungs and potentially other parts of their body.

I love Vice's content, so I say this as a fan. Step up your reporting, inform us more, and ask harder questions if you're going to frame this video as "The Netherlands Is Letting People Get Sick to Beat Coronavirus ."

snippet.textDisplay:
RE Verena Tavares’s comment one hour ago:


The video is most certainly NOT inaccurate.


And if VICE NEWS is misleading us, then why does Netherland’s own media report that what the Dutch government is in fact pursuing is a “herd immunity” trial, as noted below.


‘Group immunity is absolutely not an aim in itself,’ Van Dissel said at a meeting with MPs ahead of Wednesday afternoon’s debate. … Nevertheless, the advantage of developing immunity is that it strengthens the impact of other measures, Van Dissels said. In the meantime, a vaccine could be developed to protect everyone. That, he told MPs, is the ultimate aim.


Check the hyperlink yourself.


https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2020/03/group-immunity-not-main-aim-of-dutch-anti-corona-measures-says-health-chief/


The story was also covered by an editorial opinion column in The New York Times, though in their case, David L. Katz MD spoke approvingly of the practice. Sheesh! What it be fair to ask Dr. Katz if he would be willing to go exposure and to initiate the herd response? Yes. But I think he might try to change the subject of the question to avoid answering the question.


The Times’ hyperlink:


https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/20/opinion/coronavirus-pandemic-social-distancing.html?0p19G=2870
